Introduction

KickFlip is a seven-member boy group formed by JYP Entertainment through the SBS survival show LOUD. The group made their debut on January 20, 2025, with their first mini album Flip it, Kick it!, featuring the title track "Mama Said". They released their pre-debut single "Umm Great" on January 6, 2025.

The group was formed through LOUD, a survival show that aired in 2021 and was co-produced by J.Y. Park of JYP Entertainment and PSY of P Nation. The original members selected for KickFlip included Yoon Min, Kyehoon, Amaru, Keiju, and Donghyeon. However, Yoon Min left the group before their debut. After some delays, KickFlip confirmed their debut in January 2025, revealing all seven members, including Donghwa, Juwang, and Minje, in early January.
